      "span_text": "His well-known protocol established that it is necessary to have bone volume, a sterile and biocompatible implant, an atraumatic surgery, implant with primary stability, and lack of functional loading during the healing period for successful osseointegration. These guidelines were a breakthrough because they allowed for more predictable implantsupported rehabilitations."
